The paper focuses on the use of neuro-evolution and neural architecture search algorithms to analyze and compare recurrent neural networks (RNNs) for time series prediction. This falls under the category of neural networks and machine learning, which is covered by several sub-categories in arXiv CS. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely sub-category as it specifically deals with the use of evolutionary algorithms for neural network optimization. cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely as they cover general topics related to machine learning and AI, which are relevant to the paper. cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible sub-category as it covers topics related to control systems, which are relevant to time series prediction. Finally, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a less likely sub-category, but still possible as it covers topics related to image and video analysis, which can also involve the use of RNNs.
